@node "Intr" "Introduction"
This little rexx  script  will  take  your  MiniCallerslog  (from
Samilog)  and  allow  you  to  output a lastcallers bulletin with
personalised borders and colours.

Yes,  Samilog does the same. Except it doesn't let you change the
colours, unless you dive in with a binary editor.

This is public domain, but this time I ask  that  you  make  DAMN
sure you  put 'P0T-NOoDLE/Samilog-v2.00/Etc' in your personalised
border. I did not write this to shit on Mr Noodle.

This  was  mainly  inspired  by  Venom and his NVX-AWAIT program,
which does a similar thing.

@endnode
@node "spec" "Specifications"
Mo-Email is currently running on my:  A1200/020/882
                                      10 Meg RAM
                                      85 Meg Drive
                                      /X version 4.#?

It should run with S!X etc as it's not BBS specific.

@endnode
@node "Impo" "Important!"
When first run it will create a new LCallers bulletin. Make  sure
all  files  are  where they should be, as I haven't programmed in
any safety checks etc. Run it from a shell as a first test.

 bbs:utils/MCS.rexx -c              Clears LC bulletin
 bbs:utils/MCS.rexx ?               Useless Information

If you don't want the Sysop to appear  in  LastCallers  then  you
define this via Samilog.

samilog -USC"etc"10 <--- remove the 'S'

Or something like that.

Needs: rexxtricks.library
@endnode
